body:
This allows conversion HashMap to/from BolType for the user to be able to retrieve arbitrary output from the graph. 

This is useful for queries like:
```cypher
MATCH (n:Model) 
  OPTIONAL MATCH (n)-[:LeftLink]->(left)
  OPTIONAL MATCH (n)-[:RightLink]->(right) 
  RETURN collect({{ node:n, left:left, right:right }}) as res;
```

Usage:
```rust 
let maps = row.get::<Vec<HashMap<String, Node>>>("res").unwrap();
for map in maps {
    let node = map.get("node");
    let left = map.get("left");
    let right = map.get("right");
    println!{"Node: {node:?}");
    println!("Left: {left:?)");
    println!("Right: {right:?}");
}
```


I created this out of a need for it as I saw there wasnt the ability to do things like this. If this is already possible another way I would love to know, otherwise I feel this could be a useful addition.
